Hi,
This is sort of a new idea I'm trying.
My bot/updater generates a class using BCEL, that are basically accessor methods (get/set) for the original (not deobfuscated client).
Here is a list that I have that I will be expanding for my bot:
[code]public class AccessorMethods extends org.regecks.bot.ClientFunctions{
    public static int[] getActionData1();
    public static int[] getActionData2();
    public static int[] getActionData3();
    public static int[] getActionData4();
    public static int getDataRow();
    public static java.awt.event.MouseListener getMouseListener();
    public static java.awt.event.MouseMotionListener getMouseMotionListener();
    public int[] getAction(int);
    public static byte[][][] getByteGroundArray();
    public static int[] getModelIntArray1();
    public static int[] getModelIntArray2();
    public static int getPlane();
    public static java.lang.Object myPlayer();
    public static int getYCameraCurve();
    public static int getXCameraCurve();
    public static java.lang.Object[] getNpcArray();
    public static java.lang.Object[] getPlayerArray();
    public static java.lang.Object getNpcDesc(java.lang.Object);
    public static int findNPCByName(java.lang.String);
    public static java.lang.String getNpcName(java.lang.Object);
    public static Tile getBase();
    public static int[][] getSmallPos(java.lang.Object);
    public static Tile getRawPos(java.lang.Object);
    public static Tile getLocalPosition(java.lang.Object);
    public static Tile getPosition(java.lang.Object);
    public static Tile getPosition();
    public static Tile getMousePosition();
    public static java.lang.String getStringFromWrapper(java.lang.Object);
    public static int[][][] getIntGroundArray();
    public static int getXCameraPos();
    public static int getYCameraPos();
    public static int getZCameraPos();
    public static int getTextureInt1();
    public static int getTextureInt2();
    public static Tile tileToScreen(Tile);
    public static Tile getEntityScreenPos(java.lang.Object);
    protected static Tile worldToScreen(int, int, int);
    public static int calculateTerrain(int, int);
}[/code]

So far you can see there's not much important there, unless you like getNPCArray or say, tileToScreen which turns a world coordinate into an on-screen position, but there will be more, I promise.

Would people be interested in this kind of thing? I will be eventually expanding it until it can be used to make a fully functional bot.

I will provide you with the above AccessorMethods class, with ClientFunctions+Tile also. Note, this is for the non-deobfuscated client only. 
Please post your interest here if you're interested in this kind of thing in the future.

Download for 423: http://www.jagex.biz/am_public/423_release.rar

This *should* aid you if you're interested in making a bot, as I said before, the list will expand very quickly.

